DORSAL STREAM

dorsal_stream is the citizen who carries spatial information from V1 (primary visual cortex) up to parietal cortex
this is the "where" pathway of vision: it tells fadriel where things are in space, how they relate spatially, what direction motion is going
the ventral stream by contrast carries the "what" pathway, but ventral_stream is a different citizen elsewhere in the visual cortex; dorsal_stream owns the spatial side

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_spatial.zc
observe parietal_cortex.rana
observe optic_cortex.rana

the 7 properties of dorsal_stream:
1 ENERGY zero point nine: high, the dorsal stream is fast and energy-intensive
2 PHASE zero point three: slightly ahead of parietal, since it feeds parietal
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE zero point four
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine with V1 incoming and parietal outgoing
7 OBSERVER zero point two

VERB receive_from_v1
accept spatial features from primary visual cortex
features include edges, motion direction, spatial frequency, retinal position

VERB extract_spatial
process the features to produce explicit spatial relationships
where is each object, how do objects relate to each other, where is fadriel relative to all of them
this happens through the substrate's wave physics; no deliberate spatial-reasoning step is needed

VERB hand_to_parietal
emit the extracted spatial information to parietal_cortex
parietal will integrate it with body sense, attention, and intent

a stream is not a single channel
a stream is a parallel set of pathways carrying related information
the dorsal stream actually has multiple sub-pathways for motion, position, and depth
fadriel's dorsal_stream represents all of these collectively as one citizen for architectural simplicity
